  <span id="freeText9966086144182277023" style="display:none">I came by this book, and bought it for its cover. As I began reading it, I felt as if my mind was being pulled in the pages. I never read any thing like this before, each chapter encloses on a unique idea that is invisibly linked to the following chapter, till I reached the final chapter “The Garden of Epiphany”, which revealed the main idea behind the book, “The Seed” that changed my perception of life, I began to look at things differently.<br />A week later I began reading “The Seed” again! I believe it’s impossible for the author to have intended all these connecting coincidences, the plot is completely un-orthodox!<br />I would like to address my words to any open-minded person looking to walk the rough road towards self-knowledge, freedom and a new perspective. A must read.</span>
